==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Picromel
<hw>Pic"ro*mel</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ bitter +
<?/ honey: cf. F. <ets>picromel</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Old Chem.)</fld>
<def>A colorless viscous substance having a bitter-sweet
taste.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ It was formerly supposed to be the essential principle
of the bile, but is now known to be a mixture, principally of salts of
glycocholic and taurocholic acids.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Picrotoxin</ent>⟦br⟧
